arth\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Implement the following plan:\\n\\n# Benchmark: Session Start Hook Performance\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nA customer reports that the `entire hooks claude-code session-start` hook significantly slows down Claude Code startup. We need a benchmark that reproduces the customer-facing latency (full process spawn) to establish a baseline for optimization.\\n\\n## Approach\\n\\n### End-to-End Subprocess Benchmark\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/hook_bench_test.go`\\n**Build tag:** `//go:build integration`\\n\\nUses the existing integration test infrastructure (`getTestBinary()`, `TestMain` binary build, `benchutil.NewBenchRepo`) to measure real-world latency of the session-start hook.\\n\\n**Scenarios:**\\n- `SessionStart/NoSessions` — Clean repo, no prior sessions (best case)\\n- `SessionStart/1Session` — 1 existing session state file\\n- `SessionStart/5Sessions` — 5 session state files (typical user)\\n- `SessionStart/20Sessions` — 20 session state files (heavy user, worst case)\\n\\nEach benchmark:\\n1. Creates a `BenchRepo` via `benchutil.NewBenchRepo()`\\n2. Creates N session state files via `benchutil.CreateSessionState()`\\n3. Pipes `{\\\"session_id\\\":\\\"bench-session\\\",\\\"transcript_path\\\":\\\"\\\"}` to stdin\\n4. Invokes `getTestBinary() hooks claude-code session-start` as a subprocess\\n5. Measures wall-clock time (what the customer experiences)\\n\\n**Key patterns to reuse:**\\n- `benchutil.NewBenchRepo()` from `cmd/entire/cli/benchutil/benchutil.go` — creates isolated repos\\n- `benchutil.CreateSessionState()` — creates session state files\\n- `getTestBinary()` from `cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/testenv.go` — shared pre-built binary\\n- `HookRunner.runHookWithOutput()` pattern from `cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/hooks.go` — subprocess invocation with stdin\\n\\n### File to Create\\n\\n`cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/hook_bench_test.go`\\n\\n### How to Run\\n\\n```bash